==English==
===Etymology===
An Anglicisation of French [[haut-goût]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'həʊgəʊ/

===Noun===
'''hogo'''
# a strong, unpleasant [[smell]]
#:*'''1922''': Some women for instance warn you off when they have their period.  Come near.  Then get a '''hogo''' you could hang your hat on.  Like what?  Potted herrings gone stale or.  Boof!  Please keep off the grass. — James Joyce, ''Ulysses''
#:*'''1980''': He opened and let out a '''hogo''' of medicinal rum and beer.  The bad tooth was a premolar. — Anthony Burgess, ''Earthly Powers''